The Banner Hills north ridge has had wolf pack activity at disruptive levels this season. Convoy traffic on the upper approach road has taken losses — equipment, provisions, one guard with injuries that required the waystation infirmary. The postmaster's office has authorized a suppression action: find the hill wolves in the upper passages, the pack leader at the den, and the sentry wolf at the perimeter. Reduce their numbers enough that the ridge route is viable again. Three types to locate and deal with. When the pack count drops, the approach road opens back up for regular traffic.
The Banner Hills ridge is reporting clear passage for the first time this season. Convoy captains are routing through the upper approach again, and the postmaster's incident log has closed out the damage assessment. The warden corps' patrol record notes a significant reduction in wolf pack activity correlated with your engagement. The ridge is manageable again.

